# LaTeX rules

## Build layout

```
tex/**/qbt/
  _QBT__<Topic>.tex
  build/
    _QBT__<Topic>.pdf      ← build output, never edit
    aux/                   ← latexmk aux files, never edit

tex/**/soln/
  _QBT___Solns__<Topic>.tex
  build/
    _QBT___Solns__<Topic>.pdf
    aux/
```

PDFs (`tex/**/build/*.pdf`) are build outputs — **never read or edit them**.

## Autonomous error-fix loop

**Never read the entire `.tex` file.** Always start with `ReadLints`.

```
1. ReadLints on the .tex file → get error message + line number
2. Read ±10 lines around the reported line
   ⚠ LaTeX error lines are often off by 1–2 lines — always consider adjacent lines
3. StrReplace → apply the minimal fix
4. Shell: rebuild (synchronous, block until done):

   latexmk -f -pdf -cd -interaction=nonstopmode -synctex=1 -file-line-error `
     -auxdir=<outdir>/aux -outdir=<outdir> <texfile>

   <outdir> = sibling "build" directory relative to the .tex file
   Example: tex/further-maths/differential-equations/qbt/build

5. ReadLints again → confirm no [ERROR] entries remain
   • Errors remain → go to step 2 for the next error
   • "Label(s) may have changed" / rerun warnings → NOT errors, ignore
```

## `\marks` command

`\marks[offset]{n}` — margin note with mark count `n`; `offset` shifts vertically.

```latex
% ✅ GOOD
\item Solve the equation. \marks{3}

% ❌ BAD — spurious \\ → "No line here to end"
\item Solve the equation. \marks{3} \\
```

**Never** place `\\` immediately after `\marks` before `\end{enumerate}` or `\item`.

## Common error patterns

| Message | Cause |
|---------|-------|
| `No line here to end` | Spurious `\\` after `\marks` or at list end |
| `\begin{...} ended by \end{...}` | Mismatched environment |
| `Missing $ inserted` | Unmatched math delimiter |
| `Missing \right.` | `\left` without matching `\right` |
| `Undefined control sequence` | Misspelled command or missing `\usepackage` |

## latexmk args reference

From `.vscode/settings.json` (keep in sync if settings change):

```
-pdf -cd -interaction=nonstopmode -synctex=1 -file-line-error
-auxdir=<OUTDIR>/aux -outdir=<OUTDIR> <DOCFILE>
```

Add `-f` when running from shell to force rebuild.
